-- Schulte Roth Hires Ex-Goldman Lawyer for Regulatory Practice
-- B y   I a n   T h o m a s
-- 2012-01-17T22:38:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/schulte-roth-hires-ex-goldman-lawyer-brad-caswell-for-regulatory-practice.html
Schulte Roth & Zabel LLP  hired Brad Caswell, a former assistant general counsel at  Goldman Sachs
Group (GS) , to help the New York-based law firm expand its regulatory
and compliance practice.  Caswell, 41, who most recently was general counsel and
chief compliance officer at City on a Hill Capital LP, has
worked for numerous hedge funds, private-equity funds and
managed accounts, Marc Elovitz, head of the firm’s 70-attorney
regulatory and compliance practice, said in a statement. In
addition to Goldman Sachs, Caswell also has worked at DKR
Capital Partners LP and DKR Oasis Management Co.  “Brad’s in-house experience as general counsel and chief
compliance officer, as well as his years of advising private
investment firms, will complement the capabilities of our
practice,” Elovitz said in the statement.  Caswell will be based in  New York  and work as a special
counsel to hedge funds and private-equity funds on operational,
regulatory and compliance matters, according to the statement.  Schulte Roth & Zabel has offices in New York, Washington
and  London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Thomas in New York at 
 ithomas15@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
